"use strict";(globalThis.webpackChunkblog_v1=globalThis.webpackChunkblog_v1||[]).push([[5117],{8621(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"/2026/09/25/web3-security-checklist-2026","metadata":{"permalink":"/en/2026/09/25/web3-security-checklist-2026","editUrl":"https://github.com/pfyangf/pfyangf.github.io/tree/main/blog/2026/09-25-web3-security-checklist-2026.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2026/09-25-web3-security-checklist-2026.md","title":"web3-security-checklist-2026","description":"","date":"2026-09-25T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":1.56,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"account-abstraction-security","permalink":"/en/2026/07/08/account-abstraction-security"}},"content":"```markdown\\n---\\nslug: web3-security-checklist-2026\\ntitle: 2026 Web3 Security Checklist\\nauthors: [autosec]\\ntags: [security check, Web3, best practices]\\ndate: 2026-09-25T10:00\\n---\\n\\nA comprehensive Web3 security checklist to help developers and users enhance security awareness.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Developer Checklist\\n\\n### Smart Contract Development\\n\\n- [ ] Use the latest version of Solidity.\\n- [ ] Follow the Checks-Effects-Interactions pattern.\\n- [ ] Implement access controls.\\n- [ ] Add event logging.\\n- [ ] Write comprehensive test cases.\\n\\n### Security Audits\\n\\n- [ ] Static analysis tool scanning.\\n- [ ] Third-party security audits.\\n- [ ] Bug bounty program.\\n- [ ] Fuzz testing.\\n- [ ] Formal verification (for critical contracts).\\n\\n### Pre-Deployment\\n\\n- [ ] Thorough testing on testnets.\\n- [ ] Prepare emergency pause mechanisms.\\n- [ ] Set up monitoring and alerts.\\n- [ ] Prepare an incident response plan.\\n- [ ] Complete documentation.\\n\\n## User Checklist\\n\\n### Wallet Security\\n\\n- [ ] Use hardware wallets for storing large amounts of assets.\\n- [ ] Backup seed phrases (store offline).\\n- [ ] Enable wallet security features.\\n- [ ] Regularly update wallet software.\\n- [ ] Diversify risk using different wallets.\\n\\n### Transaction Security\\n\\n- [ ] Verify website URLs.\\n- [ ] Check contract addresses.\\n- [ ] Understand transaction content before signing.\\n- [ ] Set reasonable slippage tolerance.\\n- [ ] Test new protocols with small amounts.\\n\\n### Daily Habits\\n\\n- [ ] Avoid transacting over public WiFi.\\n- [ ] Regularly review authorizations.\\n- [ ] Follow official project announcements.\\n- [ ] Stay updated on the latest security knowledge.\\n- [ ] Maintain a skeptical attitude.\\n\\n## Project Team Checklist\\n\\n### Security Operations\\n\\n- [ ] Establish a security team.\\n- [ ] Conduct regular security training.\\n- [ ] Implement a bug bounty program.\\n- [ ] Prepare an incident response process.\\n- [ ] Purchase security insurance.\\n\\n### User Education\\n\\n- [ ] Provide security usage guides.\\n- [ ] Warn about common scam methods.\\n- [ ] Establish official communication channels.\\n- [ ] Timely release security announcements.\\n\\n## Emergency Response\\n\\n### When a Vulnerability is Discovered\\n\\n1. Immediately pause the contract (if such functionality exists).\\n2. Notify users.\\n3. Contact the security team.\\n4. Prepare a remediation plan.\\n5. Communicate transparently.\\n\\n### When Assets are Stolen\\n\\n1. Immediately transfer remaining assets.\\n2. Report to relevant platforms.\\n3. Contact law enforcement.\\n4. Track fund flows.\\n5. Summarize lessons learned.\\n\\n## Conclusion\\n\\nSecurity is an ongoing process that requires the joint effort of all participants. Regularly review and update this checklist to stay vigilant.\\n```"},{"id":"/2026/07/08/account-abstraction-security","metadata":{"permalink":"/en/2026/07/08/account-abstraction-security","editUrl":"https://github.com/pfyangf/pfyangf.github.io/tree/main/blog/2026/07-08-account-abstraction-security.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2026/07-08-account-abstraction-security.md","title":"account-abstraction-security","description":"","date":"2026-07-08T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.98,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"web3-security-checklist-2026","permalink":"/en/2026/09/25/web3-security-checklist-2026"},"nextItem":{"title":"mev-protection-strategies","permalink":"/en/2026/05/12/mev-protection-strategies"}},"content":"```markdown\\n---\\nslug: account-abstraction-security\\ntitle: Account Abstraction Security Analysis\\nauthors: [autosec]\\ntags: [account abstraction, ERC-4337, security]\\ndate: 2026-07-08T10:00\\n---\\n\\nAccount Abstraction is transforming the Ethereum user experience but also introduces new security considerations.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## What is Account Abstraction?\\n\\nAccount Abstraction allows smart contract wallets to possess the same capabilities as EOAs (Externally Owned Accounts), providing more flexible account management.\\n\\n## ERC-4337 Standard\\n\\n### Core Concepts\\n\\n- **UserOperation**: An expression of user intent.\\n- **Bundler**: Packages and submits transactions.\\n- **EntryPoint**: A unified entry contract.\\n- **Paymaster**: Pays gas fees on behalf of users.\\n\\n## Security Advantages\\n\\n### 1. Social Recovery\\n\\nRecover accounts through trusted contacts without needing a seed phrase.\\n\\n### 2. Multi-Signature Authorization\\n\\nCritical operations require multiple signatures.\\n\\n### 3. Custom Validation Logic\\n\\nSupports various authentication methods.\\n\\n## Security Risks\\n\\n### Paymaster Risks\\n\\nA malicious Paymaster could potentially steal user funds.\\n\\n### Signature Validation Vulnerabilities\\n\\nCustom validation logic may contain vulnerabilities.\\n\\n## Best Practices\\n\\n1. Use audited Account Abstraction wallets.\\n2. Choose Paymasters cautiously.\\n3. Set reasonable spending limits.\\n4. Regularly review authorizations.\\n\\n## Main Implementations\\n\\n- **Safe**: Multi-signature smart contract wallet.\\n- **Argent**: Social recovery wallet.\\n- **Biconomy**: AA infrastructure.\\n\\n## Conclusion\\n\\nAccount Abstraction offers a better user experience, but understanding its security model is essential.\\n```"},{"id":"/2026/05/12/mev-protection-strategies","metadata":{"permalink":"/en/2026/05/12/mev-protection-strategies","editUrl":"https://github.com/pfyangf/pfyangf.github.io/tree/main/blog/2026/05-12-mev-protection-strategies.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2026/05-12-mev-protection-strategies.md","title":"mev-protection-strategies","description":"","date":"2026-05-12T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.97,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"account-abstraction-security","permalink":"/en/2026/07/08/account-abstraction-security"},"nextItem":{"title":"zero-knowledge-proofs-intro","permalink":"/en/2026/03/20/zero-knowledge-proofs-intro"}},"content":"```markdown\\n---\\nslug: mev-protection-strategies\\ntitle: MEV Protection Strategies\\nauthors: [autosec]\\ntags: [MEV, DeFi, transaction protection]\\ndate: 2026-05-12T10:00\\n---\\n\\nMEV (Miner Extractable Value) has a significant impact on DeFi users. Learn how to protect yourself from MEV attacks.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## What is MEV?\\n\\nMEV refers to the extra profit miners or validators can extract by reordering, inserting, or censoring transactions.\\n\\n## Common MEV Attacks\\n\\n### 1. Front-running\\n\\nAn attacker sees your transaction and executes a similar one with a higher gas fee to get priority.\\n\\n### 2. Sandwich Attacks\\n\\nInserting trades before and after your transaction to manipulate the price for profit.\\n\\n## Protection Measures\\n\\n### Using MEV Protection Tools\\n\\n- **Flashbots Protect**: Private transaction pool.\\n- **CowSwap**: MEV-protected DEX.\\n- **1inch Fusion**: MEV-resistant trades.\\n\\n### Trading Strategies\\n\\n1. Set reasonable slippage tolerance.\\n2. Execute large trades in smaller batches.\\n3. Use limit orders instead of market orders.\\n\\n## Technical Principles\\n\\n### Flashbots\\n\\nAvoids public monitoring of transactions through a private mempool.\\n\\n### Order Flow Auctions\\n\\nAllows users to benefit from MEV rather than be exploited by it.\\n\\n## Future Developments\\n\\n- PBS (Proposer-Builder Separation).\\n- Encrypted mempools.\\n- Fair ordering protocols.\\n\\n## Conclusion\\n\\nUnderstanding MEV and taking protective measures can help reduce trading losses.\\n```"},{"id":"/2026/03/20/zero-knowledge-proofs-intro","metadata":{"permalink":"/en/2026/03/20/zero-knowledge-proofs-intro","editUrl":"https://github.com/pfyangf/pfyangf.github.io/tree/main/blog/2026/03-20-zero-knowledge-proofs-intro.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2026/03-20-zero-knowledge-proofs-intro.md","title":"zero-knowledge-proofs-intro","description":"","date":"2026-03-20T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.79,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"mev-protection-strategies","permalink":"/en/2026/05/12/mev-protection-strategies"},"nextItem":{"title":"ai-blockchain-security","permalink":"/en/2026/01/15/ai-blockchain-security"}},"content":"```markdown\\n---\\nslug: zero-knowledge-proofs-intro\\ntitle: Introduction to Zero-Knowledge Proofs\\nauthors: [autosec]\\ntags: [zero-knowledge proofs, privacy, ZK]\\ndate: 2026-03-20T10:00\\n---\\n\\nZero-Knowledge Proofs (ZKPs) are a key technology for privacy protection in blockchain.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## What Are Zero-Knowledge Proofs?\\n\\nZero-Knowledge Proofs allow one party (the prover) to prove to another party (the verifier) that a statement is true, without revealing any additional information.\\n\\n## Application Scenarios\\n\\n### 1. Private Transactions\\n\\nVerify transaction validity without disclosing transaction details.\\n\\n### 2. Identity Authentication\\n\\nProve identity without revealing specific information.\\n\\n## Key Technologies\\n\\n### zk-SNARKs\\n\\n- Succinct proofs.\\n- Fast verification.\\n- Requires a trusted setup.\\n\\n### zk-STARKs\\n\\n- No trusted setup required.\\n- Quantum-resistant.\\n- Larger proof size.\\n\\n## Real-World Projects\\n\\n- **Zcash**: Privacy-focused cryptocurrency.\\n- **zkSync**: Layer 2 scaling solution.\\n- **Polygon zkEVM**: EVM-compatible ZK Rollup.\\n\\n## Learning Resources\\n\\n- ZK Whiteboard Sessions\\n- ZK Hack\\n- 0xPARC Courses\\n\\n## Conclusion\\n\\nZero-Knowledge Proofs represent a crucial direction for blockchain technology development and are worth deep exploration.\\n```"},{"id":"/2026/01/15/ai-blockchain-security","metadata":{"permalink":"/en/2026/01/15/ai-blockchain-security","editUrl":"https://github.com/pfyangf/pfyangf.github.io/tree/main/blog/2026/01-15-ai-blockchain-security.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2026/01-15-ai-blockchain-security.md","title":"ai-blockchain-security","description":"","date":"2026-01-15T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.84,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"zero-knowledge-proofs-intro","permalink":"/en/2026/03/20/zero-knowledge-proofs-intro"},"nextItem":{"title":"crypto-wallet-recovery","permalink":"/en/2025/11/25/crypto-wallet-recovery"}},"content":"```markdown\\n---\\nslug: ai-blockchain-security\\ntitle: The Integration of AI and Blockchain Security\\nauthors: [autosec]\\ntags: [AI, blockchain security, artificial intelligence]\\ndate: 2026-01-15T10:00\\n---\\n\\nExplore how artificial intelligence is transforming the field of blockchain security and future development trends.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Applications of AI in Security Auditing\\n\\n### Automated Vulnerability Detection\\n\\nAI can quickly scan smart contract code to identify potential vulnerabilities.\\n\\n### Pattern Recognition\\n\\nMachine learning algorithms can identify abnormal transaction patterns.\\n\\n## Practical Applications\\n\\n### 1. Smart Contract Auditing\\n\\nAI-assisted auditing tools can:\\n- Detect common vulnerability patterns.\\n- Generate test cases.\\n- Provide remediation suggestions.\\n\\n### 2. Threat Detection\\n\\nMonitor blockchain transactions in real-time to identify suspicious activities.\\n\\n## Challenges and Limitations\\n\\n- AI models require extensive training data.\\n- Potential for false positives.\\n- Cannot fully replace manual audits.\\n\\n## Future Outlook\\n\\nAI will play a larger role in:\\n- Predictive security analysis.\\n- Automated incident response.\\n- Intelligent risk assessment.\\n\\n## Recommended Tools\\n\\n- **Certik**: AI-powered auditing platform.\\n- **Forta**: AI threat detection network.\\n\\n## Conclusion\\n\\nThe integration of AI and blockchain security will open up new possibilities.\\n```"},{"id":"/2025/11/25/crypto-wallet-recovery","metadata":{"permalink":"/en/2025/11/25/crypto-wallet-recovery","editUrl":"https://github.com/pfyangf/pfyangf.github.io/tree/main/blog/2025/11-25-crypto-wallet-recovery.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025/11-25-crypto-wallet-recovery.md","title":"crypto-wallet-recovery","description":"","date":"2025-11-25T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":1.05,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"ai-blockchain-security","permalink":"/en/2026/01/15/ai-blockchain-security"},"nextItem":{"title":"dao-governance-security","permalink":"/en/2025/09/30/dao-governance-security"}},"content":"```markdown\\n---\\nslug: crypto-wallet-recovery\\ntitle: Cryptocurrency Wallet Recovery Guide\\nauthors: [autosec]\\ntags: [wallet recovery, seed phrase, security]\\ndate: 2025-11-25T10:00\\n---\\n\\nLearn how to securely back up and restore cryptocurrency wallets to prevent permanent asset loss.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Backup Methods\\n\\n### 1. Seed Phrase Backup\\n\\nA 12 or 24-word seed phrase is the key to wallet recovery.\\n\\n### 2. Private Key Backup\\n\\nDirectly backing up the private key (not recommended for beginners).\\n\\n## Secure Storage\\n\\n### Physical Storage\\n\\n- Engraved metal plates.\\n- Paper backups (waterproof and fire-resistant).\\n- Safe deposit box storage.\\n\\n### Digital Storage (Use with Caution)\\n\\n- Encrypted USB drives.\\n- Password managers (offline).\\n\\n## Recovery Steps\\n\\n1. Download the official wallet application.\\n2. Select the \\"Restore Wallet\\" option.\\n3. Enter the seed phrase in the correct order.\\n4. Set a new password.\\n5. Verify that the addresses are correct.\\n\\n## Common Mistakes\\n\\n- Entering seed words in the wrong order.\\n- Spelling errors.\\n- Using an incorrect derivation path.\\n\\n## Security Tips\\n\\n\u26a0\ufe0f **Never**:\\n- Store your seed phrase online.\\n- Save photos of your seed phrase.\\n- Share your seed phrase with others.\\n\\n## Test Recovery\\n\\nIt is recommended to test the recovery process with a small amount of funds to ensure the backup is effective.\\n\\n## Conclusion\\n\\nA proper backup and recovery process is the last line of defense in protecting your assets.\\n```"},{"id":"/2025/09/30/dao-governance-security","metadata":{"permalink":"/en/2025/09/30/dao-governance-security","editUrl":"https://github.com/pfyangf/pfyangf.github.io/tree/main/blog/2025/09-30-dao-governance-security.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025/09-30-dao-governance-security.md","title":"dao-governance-security","description":"","date":"2025-09-30T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.76,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"crypto-wallet-recovery","permalink":"/en/2025/11/25/crypto-wallet-recovery"},"nextItem":{"title":"layer2-security-analysis","permalink":"/en/2025/07/22/layer2-security-analysis"}},"content":"```markdown\\n---\\nslug: dao-governance-security\\ntitle: DAO Governance Security Guide\\nauthors: [autosec]\\ntags: [DAO, governance, security]\\ndate: 2025-09-30T10:00\\n---\\n\\nDAO (Decentralized Autonomous Organization) governance security is crucial. This article explores security issues in DAO governance.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## DAO Governance Risks\\n\\n### 1. Governance Attacks\\n\\nAttackers gain control of a DAO by acquiring a large number of governance tokens.\\n\\n### 2. Proposal Vulnerabilities\\n\\nMalicious proposals can lead to fund loss.\\n\\n## Security Mechanisms\\n\\n### Timelocks\\n\\nEnsure sufficient time for community review before a proposal is executed.\\n\\n### Multi-signature Wallets\\n\\nCritical operations require approval from multiple signers.\\n\\n## Best Practices\\n\\n1. **Set Reasonable Proposal Thresholds**\\n2. **Implement Voting Delay Mechanisms**\\n3. **Establish Emergency Pause Functionality**\\n4. **Conduct Regular Security Audits**\\n\\n## Case Studies\\n\\nAnalysis of several DAO governance attack cases:\\n- Flash loan governance attacks.\\n- Proposal execution vulnerabilities.\\n\\n## Recommended Tools\\n\\n- **Snapshot**: Off-chain voting platform.\\n- **Tally**: DAO governance dashboard.\\n\\n## Conclusion\\n\\nDAO governance requires a balance between decentralization and security.\\n```"},{"id":"/2025/07/22/layer2-security-analysis","metadata":{"permalink":"/en/2025/07/22/layer2-security-analysis","editUrl":"https://github.com/pfyangf/pfyangf.github.io/tree/main/blog/2025/07-22-layer2-security-analysis.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025/07-22-layer2-security-analysis.md","title":"layer2-security-analysis","description":"","date":"2025-07-22T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.73,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"dao-governance-security","permalink":"/en/2025/09/30/dao-governance-security"},"nextItem":{"title":"smart-contract-audit-process","permalink":"/en/2025/04/18/smart-contract-audit-process"}},"content":"```markdown\\n---\\nslug: layer2-security-analysis\\ntitle: Layer 2 Security Analysis\\nauthors: [autosec]\\ntags: [Layer2, scaling, security]\\ndate: 2025-07-22T10:00\\n---\\n\\nLayer 2 solutions are rapidly evolving, but they also introduce new security considerations.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Layer 2 Types\\n\\n### Rollups\\n\\n- **Optimistic Rollups**: Optimistic execution.\\n- **ZK Rollups**: Zero-knowledge proofs.\\n\\n### State Channels\\n\\nPeer-to-peer off-chain transaction channels.\\n\\n## Security Risks\\n\\n### 1. Bridging Risks\\n\\nAsset bridges between Layer 1 and Layer 2 are hotspots for attacks.\\n\\n### 2. Sequencer Centralization\\n\\nSequencers in most Layer 2 solutions are centralized.\\n\\n## Security Recommendations\\n\\n- Understand the security models of different Layer 2 solutions.\\n- Diversify assets; do not store all funds on a single Layer 2.\\n- Monitor the decentralization roadmaps of projects.\\n\\n## Major Layer 2 Solutions\\n\\n- **Arbitrum**: Optimistic Rollup.\\n- **Optimism**: Optimistic Rollup.\\n- **zkSync**: ZK Rollup.\\n- **StarkNet**: ZK Rollup.\\n\\n## Conclusion\\n\\nLayer 2 offers scaling solutions, but it\'s crucial to understand their security trade-offs.\\n```"},{"id":"/2025/04/18/smart-contract-audit-process","metadata":{"permalink":"/en/2025/04/18/smart-contract-audit-process","editUrl":"https://github.com/pfyangf/pfyangf.github.io/tree/main/blog/2025/04-18-smart-contract-audit-process.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025/04-18-smart-contract-audit-process.md","title":"smart-contract-audit-process","description":"","date":"2025-04-18T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.68,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"layer2-security-analysis","permalink":"/en/2025/07/22/layer2-security-analysis"},"nextItem":{"title":"Guide to Preventing Web3 Phishing Attacks","permalink":"/en/web3-phishing-attacks"}},"content":"```markdown\\n---\\nslug: smart-contract-audit-process\\ntitle: Detailed Explanation of the Smart Contract Audit Process\\nauthors: [autosec]\\ntags: [audit, smart contract, security]\\ndate: 2025-04-18T10:00\\n---\\n\\nUnderstand the complete smart contract audit process to ensure the code is secure and reliable.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Audit Process\\n\\n### 1. Preparation Phase\\n\\n- Collect project documentation.\\n- Understand the business logic.\\n- Define the audit scope.\\n\\n### 2. Code Review\\n\\n- Manual code review.\\n- Automated tool scanning.\\n- Test case verification.\\n\\n### 3. Report Generation\\n\\n- Vulnerability classification.\\n- Remediation recommendations.\\n- Best practice suggestions.\\n\\n## Common Tools\\n\\n- **Slither**: Static analysis tool.\\n- **Mythril**: Symbolic execution engine.\\n- **Echidna**: Fuzzing tool.\\n\\n## Audit Checklist\\n\\n- [ ] Reentrancy attack check.\\n- [ ] Access control verification.\\n- [ ] Integer overflow detection.\\n- [ ] External call security.\\n\\n## Selecting an Audit Firm\\n\\n- Review past audit cases.\\n- Understand the team\'s background.\\n- Compare pricing and timelines.\\n\\n## Conclusion\\n\\nProfessional security audits are a necessary step before deploying smart contracts.\\n```"},{"id":"web3-phishing-attacks","metadata":{"permalink":"/en/web3-phishing-attacks","editUrl":"https://github.com/pfyangf/pfyangf.github.io/tree/main/blog/2025/02-10-web3-phishing-attacks.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025/02-10-web3-phishing-attacks.md","title":"Guide to Preventing Web3 Phishing Attacks","description":"Phishing attacks are one of the greatest threats faced by Web3 users. Learn how to identify and prevent phishing attacks.","date":"2025-02-10T10:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"phishing attacks","permalink":"/en/tags/phishing-attacks"},{"inline":true,"label":"Web3 security","permalink":"/en/tags/web-3-security"},{"inline":true,"label":"protection","permalink":"/en/tags/protection"}],"readingTime":0.61,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"AutoSec Team","title":"Web3 Security Researchers","url":"https://autosec.dev","imageURL":"/en/img/autosec.logo.png","key":"autosec","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"web3-phishing-attacks","title":"Guide to Preventing Web3 Phishing Attacks","authors":["autosec"],"tags":["phishing attacks","Web3 security","protection"],"date":"2025-02-10T10:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"smart-contract-audit-process","permalink":"/en/2025/04/18/smart-contract-audit-process"},"nextItem":{"title":"blockchain-security-trends","permalink":"/en/2024/12/15/blockchain-security-trends"}},"content":"Phishing attacks are one of the greatest threats faced by Web3 users. Learn how to identify and prevent phishing attacks.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Common Phishing Tactics\\n\\n### 1. Fake Websites\\n\\nAttackers create phishing websites that closely resemble official ones.\\n\\n### 2. Malicious Signature Requests\\n\\nTricking users into signing malicious transactions.\\n\\n## Identification Tips\\n\\n- Check if the URL is correct.\\n- Verify the HTTPS certificate.\\n- Check the domain registration date.\\n\\n## Protective Measures\\n\\n1. Use bookmarks to access frequently used websites.\\n2. Enable transaction simulation features in your wallet.\\n3. Install security plugins.\\n\\n## Emergency Response\\n\\nIf you accidentally click on a phishing link:\\n- Immediately transfer your assets.\\n- Replace your wallet.\\n- Report the incident to relevant platforms.\\n\\n## Conclusion\\n\\nRemaining vigilant and cultivating good security habits can effectively prevent phishing attacks."},{"id":"/2024/12/15/blockchain-security-trends","metadata":{"permalink":"/en/2024/12/15/blockchain-security-trends","editUrl":"https://github.com/pfyangf/pfyangf.github.io/tree/main/blog/2024/12-15-blockchain-security-trends.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2024/12-15-blockchain-security-trends.md","title":"blockchain-security-trends","description":"","date":"2024-12-15T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.82,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Guide to Preventing Web3 Phishing Attacks","permalink":"/en/web3-phishing-attacks"},"nextItem":{"title":"Cryptocurrency Wallet Security Best Practices","permalink":"/en/wallet-security-best-practices"}},"content":"```markdown\\n---\\nslug: blockchain-security-trends\\ntitle: 2024 Blockchain Security Trends\\nauthors: [autosec]\\ntags: [blockchain, security trends, Web3]\\ndate: 2024-12-15T10:00\\n---\\n\\nA review of the significant trends and events in the blockchain security landscape during 2024.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Major Trends\\n\\n### 1. Cross-Chain Bridge Security\\n\\nCross-chain bridges have become primary targets for attacks, with multiple projects suffering significant losses.\\n\\n### 2. AI-Assisted Auditing\\n\\nArtificial intelligence has begun to be applied to smart contract security auditing.\\n\\n### 3. Zero-Knowledge Proofs\\n\\nZK technology has made significant strides in the field of privacy protection.\\n\\n## Major Events\\n\\n- Multiple DeFi protocols suffered flash loan attacks.\\n- Regulatory policies have gradually improved.\\n- Demand for security audits has surged.\\n\\n## Future Outlook\\n\\nFor 2025, we anticipate:\\n- More security tools and services.\\n- A more refined regulatory framework.\\n- Enhanced security awareness across the industry.\\n\\n## Recommendations\\n\\nDevelopers should:\\n- Continuously learn the latest security knowledge.\\n- Engage with the security community.\\n- Conduct comprehensive code audits.\\n\\n## Conclusion\\n\\nBlockchain security is an evolving field that requires ongoing attention.\\n```"},{"id":"wallet-security-best-practices","metadata":{"permalink":"/en/wallet-security-best-practices","editUrl":"https://github.com/pfyangf/pfyangf.github.io/tree/main/blog/2024/10-05-wallet-security-best-practices.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2024/10-05-wallet-security-best-practices.md","title":"Cryptocurrency Wallet Security Best Practices","description":"Cryptocurrency wallets are essential tools for managing digital assets. This article introduces best practices for wallet security.","date":"2024-10-05T10:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"wallet","permalink":"/en/tags/wallet"},{"inline":true,"label":"security","permalink":"/en/tags/security"},{"inline":true,"label":"private key management","permalink":"/en/tags/private-key-management"}],"readingTime":0.68,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"AutoSec Team","title":"Web3 Security Researchers","url":"https://autosec.dev","imageURL":"/en/img/autosec.logo.png","key":"autosec","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"wallet-security-best-practices","title":"Cryptocurrency Wallet Security Best Practices","authors":["autosec"],"tags":["wallet","security","private key management"],"date":"2024-10-05T10:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"blockchain-security-trends","permalink":"/en/2024/12/15/blockchain-security-trends"},"nextItem":{"title":"NFT Security Tips","permalink":"/en/nft-security-tips"}},"content":"Cryptocurrency wallets are essential tools for managing digital assets. This article introduces best practices for wallet security.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Wallet Types\\n\\n### Hot Wallet\\n\\nConnected to the internet, convenient but carries higher risks.\\n\\n### Cold Wallet\\n\\nOffline storage, offering higher security and suitable for long-term holdings.\\n\\n## Security Recommendations\\n\\n1. **Backup Your Seed Phrase**: Write it on paper and store it in a secure location.\\n2. **Use Strong Passwords**: Set a complex password.\\n3. **Enable 2FA**: Two-factor authentication adds an extra layer of security.\\n4. **Update Regularly**: Keep your wallet software up to date.\\n\\n## Common Mistakes\\n\\n- Storing seed phrases online.\\n- Transacting over public WiFi.\\n- Clicking on unknown links.\\n\\n## Recommended Wallets\\n\\n- **Hardware Wallets**: Ledger, Trezor.\\n- **Software Wallets**: MetaMask, Trust Wallet.\\n\\n## Conclusion\\n\\nWallet security is the first line of defense in protecting your assets, so it must be taken seriously."},{"id":"nft-security-tips","metadata":{"permalink":"/en/nft-security-tips","editUrl":"https://github.com/pfyangf/pfyangf.github.io/tree/main/blog/2024/08-10-nft-security-tips.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2024/08-10-nft-security-tips.md","title":"NFT Security Tips","description":"The NFT market is booming, but scams and attacks are frequent. Understanding how to use NFTs safely is crucial.","date":"2024-08-10T10:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"NFT","permalink":"/en/tags/nft"},{"inline":true,"label":"security","permalink":"/en/tags/security"},{"inline":true,"label":"digital assets","permalink":"/en/tags/digital-assets"}],"readingTime":0.52,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"AutoSec Team","title":"Web3 Security Researchers","url":"https://autosec.dev","imageURL":"/en/img/autosec.logo.png","key":"autosec","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"nft-security-tips","title":"NFT Security Tips","authors":["autosec"],"tags":["NFT","security","digital assets"],"date":"2024-08-10T10:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Cryptocurrency Wallet Security Best Practices","permalink":"/en/wallet-security-best-practices"},"nextItem":{"title":"DeFi Security Guide","permalink":"/en/defi-security-guide"}},"content":"The NFT market is booming, but scams and attacks are frequent. Understanding how to use NFTs safely is crucial.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## Common NFT Scams\\n\\n### 1. Phishing Websites\\n\\nFake NFT marketplace websites designed to steal users\' wallet credentials.\\n\\n### 2. Fake Airdrops\\n\\nScammers send links to fraudulent NFT airdrops.\\n\\n## Security Recommendations\\n\\n- **Verify Website URLs**: Ensure you are visiting the official website.\\n- **Use Hardware Wallets**: Store high-value NFTs.\\n- **Check Contract Addresses**: Verify the contract before making a transaction.\\n\\n## NFT Storage\\n\\nIt is recommended to store precious NFTs in cold wallets to avoid online risks.\\n\\n## Conclusion\\n\\nProtect your NFT assets and stay vigilant against various scam tactics."},{"id":"defi-security-guide","metadata":{"permalink":"/en/defi-security-guide","editUrl":"https://github.com/pfyangf/pfyangf.github.io/tree/main/blog/2024/06-20-defi-security-guide.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2024/06-20-defi-security-guide.md","title":"DeFi Security Guide","description":"DeFi (Decentralized Finance) is transforming the financial industry but also introduces new security challenges.","date":"2024-06-20T10:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"DeFi","permalink":"/en/tags/de-fi"},{"inline":true,"label":"security","permalink":"/en/tags/security"},{"inline":true,"label":"decentralized finance","permalink":"/en/tags/decentralized-finance"}],"readingTime":0.56,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"AutoSec Team","title":"Web3 Security Researchers","url":"https://autosec.dev","imageURL":"/en/img/autosec.logo.png","key":"autosec","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"defi-security-guide","title":"DeFi Security Guide","authors":["autosec"],"tags":["DeFi","security","decentralized finance"],"date":"2024-06-20T10:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"NFT Security Tips","permalink":"/en/nft-security-tips"},"nextItem":{"title":"Smart Contract Security Basics","permalink":"/en/smart-contract-security-basics"}},"content":"DeFi (Decentralized Finance) is transforming the financial industry but also introduces new security challenges.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## DeFi Security Risks\\n\\n### Smart Contract Risks\\n\\nDeFi protocols rely on smart contracts; any vulnerability can lead to fund loss.\\n\\n### Price Manipulation\\n\\nAttackers may manipulate price oracles through flash loans.\\n\\n## How to Protect Your Assets\\n\\n1. **Diversify Investments**: Do not allocate all funds to a single protocol.\\n2. **Use Audited Protocols**: Choose projects that have undergone security audits.\\n3. **Test with Small Amounts**: Start with a small test transaction when using a new protocol.\\n\\n## Recommended Tools\\n\\n- **DeFi Pulse**: Tracks DeFi protocols.\\n- **DeFiSafety**: Check security ratings.\\n\\n## Conclusion\\n\\nDeFi offers significant opportunities, but security issues must be approached with caution."},{"id":"smart-contract-security-basics","metadata":{"permalink":"/en/smart-contract-security-basics","editUrl":"https://github.com/pfyangf/pfyangf.github.io/tree/main/blog/2024/03-15-smart-contract-security-basics.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2024/03-15-smart-contract-security-basics.md","title":"Smart Contract Security Basics","description":"Smart contract security is at the core of blockchain development. This article introduces the fundamental concepts and common vulnerabilities of smart contract security.","date":"2024-03-15T10:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"smart contract","permalink":"/en/tags/smart-contract"},{"inline":true,"label":"security","permalink":"/en/tags/security"},{"inline":true,"label":"Solidity","permalink":"/en/tags/solidity"}],"readingTime":0.64,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"AutoSec Team","title":"Web3 Security Researchers","url":"https://autosec.dev","imageURL":"/en/img/autosec.logo.png","key":"autosec","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"smart-contract-security-basics","title":"Smart Contract Security Basics","authors":["autosec"],"tags":["smart contract","security","Solidity"],"date":"2024-03-15T10:00"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"DeFi Security Guide","permalink":"/en/defi-security-guide"}},"content":"Smart contract security is at the core of blockchain development. This article introduces the fundamental concepts and common vulnerabilities of smart contract security.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## What is a Smart Contract?\\n\\nA smart contract is a self-executing program running on the blockchain that cannot be modified once deployed.\\n\\n## Common Security Issues\\n\\n### 1. Reentrancy Attacks\\n\\nReentrancy attacks are one of the most common vulnerabilities in smart contracts.\\n\\n```solidity\\n// Insecure code example\\nfunction withdraw() public {\\n    uint amount = balances[msg.sender];\\n    msg.sender.call{value: amount}(\\"\\");\\n    balances[msg.sender] = 0;\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 2. Integer Overflow\\nInteger overflow could occur in Solidity before version 0.8.0.\\n\\nSecurity Recommendations\\nUse the latest version of Solidity\\n\\nConduct code audits\\n\\nWrite comprehensive test cases\\n\\nConclusion\\nSmart contract security requires significant attention from developers. Following best practices can help prevent most security issues."}]}}')}}]);